<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="14" PagePadding="16">
    <Section>
        <Paragraph FontSize="20" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,0,0,8">
            6.1. Setup using the charger
        </Paragraph>

        <Paragraph>
            The charge mode and charge current limit most appropriate for the battery type and capacity can be
      selected using the
            <Bold>MODE</Bold> button on the Blue Smart IP22 Charger.
        </Paragraph>

        <Paragraph>
            <Bold>To setup using the charger:</Bold>
        </Paragraph>

        <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="0,6,0,0">
            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Connect the Blue Smart IP22 Charger AC power cable to a mains power outlet; after a short delay the
          LEDs indicating the current charge mode and charge state will illuminate.
                </Paragraph>
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,16">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/setup1.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform" MaxWidth="720"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    Press (and release) the MODE button on the Blue Smart IP22 Charger to cycle through and select the
          most appropriate integrated charge mode (Normal, Normal + Recondition, High, High + Recondition or
          Li-ion).
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph Foreground="#555" FontStyle="Italic">
                    Ensure that recondition stage is only enabled when required, as unnecessary or overuse will reduce battery life.
                </Paragraph>
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,16">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/setup2.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform" MaxWidth="720"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    The LED beside the currently selected charge mode (NORMAL / HIGH / LI-ION) will be illuminated, as
          well as the RECONDITION LED if enabled.
                </Paragraph>
                <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,16">
                    <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/Assets/Manuals/setup3.png"
                 Stretch="Uniform" MaxWidth="720"/>
                </BlockUIContainer>
            </ListItem>

            <ListItem>
                <Paragraph>
                    If the maximum rated charge current is excessive, enable low current mode (charge current limited to
          50% of the maximum rated charge current and disabled fan). To enable (or disable) low current mode
          depress and hold down the MODE button on the Blue Smart IP22 Charger for 6 seconds; when enabled the
          NIGHT LED will blink.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    Alternatively night mode can be enabled, which temporarily activates low current mode for a period of
          8 hours (typically overnight to eliminate fan noise). To enable (or disable) night mode depress and
          hold down the MODE button on the Blue Smart IP22 Charger for 3 seconds; when enabled the NIGHT LED
          will be illuminated.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    <Bold>Note:</Bold> All settings are stored and will not be lost when the charger is disconnected from
          mains power or the battery.
                </Paragraph>
            </ListItem>
        </List>
    </Section>
</FlowDocument>
